<TITLE> N Korea says may stay out of nuclear curbs deal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 GENEVA, Tue May 26, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - North Korea on Tuesday criticised South Korea and Japan for denouncing its nuclear test and told a global disarmament forum this could prevent it from supporting moves to curb production of atomic bomb-making material. The United Nations-sponsored Conference on Disarmament is weighing a proposed package amid signs that it could break a decade-long deadlock. Launching negotiations to ban production of fissile material (plutonium and highly-enriched uranium) is seen as the top priority. "This delegation cannot rule out the probability that those statements might negatively effect the positive constellation in my capital toward the draft decision," North Korean diplomat An Myung Hun told the 65-nation gathering. "As long as sanctions are forced on us, we will continue to take necessary corresponding measures for defending our sovereignty and peace on the Korean peninsula by our own strength," An said. Earlier, delegations from South Korea and Japan said that the underground nuclear blast which Pyongyang conducted on Monday posed a serious challenge to regional peace and international efforts to stem the spread of atomic wea
